                            <comment id="13006572" author="ghelmling" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 18:59:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This definitely makes sense to me, as a moving average seems a much more useful metric.  So seems like we&apos;d want this for both &quot;blockCacheHitRatio&quot; and &quot;blockCacheHitCachingRatio&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an aside, we should probably not change the way that the related &quot;count&quot; metrics are reported though.  If a metrics collection setup is configured to see those as incrementing values, the displayed values freak out if they start reseting (I&apos;ve seen this with cacti at least).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006590" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 19:39:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 what Gary said.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006609" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 20:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Might be interesting to consider using something like jrobin for metrics like this - so we can get these metrics at various granularities.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006613" author="streamy" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 20:14:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is basically what is implemented over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3306&quot; title=&quot;Add better cache hit ratio statistics for LRU&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3306&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3306&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Just needs to be finished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can try to work on this over the next couple days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006628" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 20:55:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Todd You talking about displaying graphs using jrobin?  (Seems like its *GPL though &amp;#8211; dang)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006639" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2011 21:22:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ah, I didn&apos;t realize it was LGPL. bummer. jfreechart&apos;s nice too, but also LGPL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
